  ],
  "notes": [
    "Conditional group-exists explicit-empty-else boundary workloads keep one optional capture, one conditional site, and tiny haystacks so the scorecard measures helper-call overhead for the newly supported bounded explicit-empty-else conditional slice rather than regex throughput.",
    "Measured rows cover the bounded `a(b)?c(?(1)d|)` and `a(?P<word>b)?c(?(word)d|)` compile/search/fullmatch plus constant-replacement `sub()`/`subn()` paths through module and compiled-`Pattern` entrypoints, the carry-forward empty-yes-arm search row now also measures real timings, the bounded alternation-heavy explicit-empty-else `a(b)?c(?(1)(de|df)|)` / `a(?P<word>b)?c(?(word)(de|df)|)` module-search and Pattern.fullmatch probes now publish real timings, the bounded nested explicit-empty-else slice now times module and compiled-`Pattern` helpers across representative capture-present and capture-absent haystacks, and the bounded quantified explicit-empty-else `a(b)?c(?(1)d|){2}` / `a(?P<word>b)?c(?(word)d|){2}` slice now publishes representative module-search and Pattern.fullmatch timings while broader quantified or backtracking-heavier conditional shapes stay as explicit gaps.",
    "Assertion-conditioned branches remain outside this benchmark manifest because CPython rejects them and the current benchmark harness only publishes timing rows for accepted syntax."
  ],
  "defaults": {
    "warmup_iterations": 2,
    "sample_iterations": 5,
    "timed_samples": 7
  },
